						<h1 class="entry-title"><a href="single.html" rel="bookmark">DC Motor Driver <small>Experience</small></a></h1>
					</header>
					<div class="entry-content" style="text-align: justify">
            <p style="text-align: justify">
            Ever since my brother introduced me to electrolincs a few years ago,
            I've been doing a lot of projects involving motors, transistors,
            pasive and active components, as well as programming. One of my most
            succesful was the development of an <i>H-bridge</i>, let's one
            control the speed and direction of rotation of a motor. Although I
            was a bit challenge for me initially, thourough planning and
            research led to me the development of my own circuit. I also
            designed a custom <i>PCB</i> for it, which turned out pretty well,
            as we can see in the following image.
            </p>

								<!-- Carousel indicators -->
